A week before tournament play gets underway, the field is nearly set for the Valspar Championship March 14-20 at Innisbrook Golf Resort in Palm Harbor. An already competitive field grew even more so with the addition of world No. 3 Viktor Hovland. Hovland will join 20 of the world’s top 50 players on the Copperhead Course, including No. 2 Collin Morikawa, No. 8 Justin Thomas and No. 9 Dustin Johnson. Defending champion Sam Burns, ranked 17th, will compete, as well. The deadline for entry is Friday at 5 p.m. Hovland, 24, of Norway tied for third in last year’s tournament and has won three events since joining the PGA Tour in 2019, including the World Wide Technology Championship at Mayakoba in November in Riviera Maya, Mexico. In addition to Hovland, No. 36 Shane Lowry and No. 62 Alex Noren also committed to the field Wednesday. Lowry last competed at the Valspar Championship in 2018, placing in a tie for 49th. Noren tied for 21st last year. Tournament play run run from March 17-20. Ticket information can be found online at valsparchampionship.com/tickets-packages/. Contact Mari Faiello at mfaiello@tampabay.com. Follow @faiello_mari.